<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="consider-v">consider <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kən'sɪdə(r)/    美 /kən'sɪdər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(仔细) 考虑：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Consider carefully before you decide.
慎重考虑后再作决定。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We have considered your application carefully, but cannot offer you the job.
我们已经认真地考虑了你的申请，认为不能聘请你做这份工作。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>consider doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As early as 1966, biologists asked the government to consider reintroducing wolves to Yellowstone Park.
早在1966年，生物学家就请求政府考虑让狼回归黄石公园。</p><footer>2017 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To turn your weakness into strength, consider taking hands-on learning or training.
要把弱项变为强项，可以考虑参加实践性学习或培训。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>consider + wh- 从句 / wh- to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Consider what you really need.
好好考虑你到底需要什么。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We must consider what to do next.
我们必须考虑下一步做什么。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>认为；觉得：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>consider ... (as / to be) sth / sb / adj:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I do not consider him as / to be the best person for the work. 
我认为他不是这项工作的最佳人选。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Neilson considers herself lucky though she suffered injuries.
尽管受了伤，尼尔森还是认为自己很幸运。</p><footer>2008 湖北</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>consider it + adj / n + to do sth：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you invite people to a party at 7 o'clock your guests will consider it polite to turn up exactly on time in Germany.
在德国，如果你邀请人们参加7点钟的聚会，客人会认为准时到场是礼貌的。</p><footer>2011 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He considered it a great honour to be invited to the party.
受邀参加聚会，他感到非常荣幸。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>consider sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Charles Babbage is generally considered to have invented the first computer.
人们普遍认为，是查尔斯•巴比奇发明了第一台电脑。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>consider + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They consider that the danger was not over.
他们认为危险还没有过去。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>体谅；顾及：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’ve got to learn to consider other people.
你得学会体谅别人。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="all-things-considered">all things considered</h3>
<p>1.<strong>考虑到所有情况；综合考虑起来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All things considered, the planned trip will have to be called off.
考虑到所有情况，计划好的旅行不得不取消了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>considered /kən'sɪdəd/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a well-considered plan
考虑周全的计划</p></div>

<p>considering /kən'sɪdərɪŋ/ prep   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Considering his ability and experience, he might have done better.
考虑到他的能力和经验，他本可以做得更好。</p><footer>2008 江西</footer></div></div>